  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#add8ff" WIDTH="150"><B>Analysis</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">We do not find, in what is here claimed<BR ALIGN='left'/>by the government to constitute a &quot;plan<BR ALIGN='left'/>of reorganization,&quot; and a<BR ALIGN='left'/>&quot;reorganization,&quot; any such transactions,<BR ALIGN='left'/>so precisely specified, so strictly<BR ALIGN='left'/>limited to the language of the statute,<BR ALIGN='left'/>and providing for such express adoption<BR ALIGN='left'/>by the corporations, as are required by<BR ALIGN='left'/>the regulations governing<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganizations under the taxing<BR ALIGN='left'/>statute. We are of the opinion that the<BR ALIGN='left'/>transactions in question did not<BR ALIGN='left'/>constitute a reorganization</TD></TR>
